# Create Tables within Assessment Questions and Answers Options

<div>Columns can be created within an <b>Assessment Question</b> and the <b>Answer Options</b>.</div><div><br></div><div>To add columns to the <b>Assessment Question</b>, use the below template/formula:</div><div><br></div><div><div>Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 | Column 4</div><div>--|--|--|--</div><div>Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 | Column 4</div><div>Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 | Column 4</div><div>Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 | Column 4</div><div>Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 | Column 4</div><div>Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 | Column 4</div><div><br></div><div>***</div></div><div><br></div><div>Question will display as follow:</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://e02.insite.com/files/sites/e02/create-tables/assessment-questions-table.png" style="width: 800px;"><br></div><div><br></div><div>To add columns in the <b>Answer Options</b>, use the <b>| </b>symbol to create the columns.<br></div><div><br></div><div>Example:</div><div><br></div><div>A.&nbsp; 1|in.</div><div>B. 10|in.</div><div>C. 5|in.</div><div>D. 15|in.</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://e02.insite.com/files/sites/e02/create-tables/assessment-questions-table-1.png" style="width: 469.004px;"><br></div><div><br></div><div>In the Settings Panel when editing a question, below&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: 700;">Option Layout</span>, select <b>Table</b> from the drop down menu. Click on the <b>Add New Column</b> button to create the columns. Select the <b>Alignment</b> (Left, Right or Center) and add the column <b>Style. </b>Select <b>Save</b> after changes were made.</div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Style Options:</b></div><div><ul><li>no-left-pad</li><li>no-right-pad<br></li><li>small-right-pad<br></li><li>small-left-pad<br></li><li>x-wide<br><br></li></ul><div><img src="https://e02.insite.com/files/sites/e02/create-tables/assessment-questions-table-4.png" style="width: 326.992px;"><br></div></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>The Answer Options will display as follow:</div><div><br></div><div><img src="https://e02.insite.com/files/sites/e02/create-tables/assessment-questions-table-5.png" style="width: 800px;"><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><b>Names</b> can be added to the columns in the <b>Answer Options</b> by adding the headings in the <b>Name</b> field under <b>Option Layout.</b></div><div><br></div><div><img src="data:image/png;base64," data-filename="image.png" style="width: 320.996px;"></div><div><br></div><div>It will display the headings as follow:<br></div><div><br></div><div><img src="data:image/png;base64," data-filename="image.png" style="width: 968.984px;"><br></div><div><br></div><div>To create wider columns, add the <b>Style</b> option <b>x-wide</b></div><div><br></div><div><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="width: 315px;" data-filename="image.png"><br></div><div><br></div><div>It will display the columns as follow:<br></div><div><br></div><div><img src="data:image/png;base64," style="width: 970.996px;" data-filename="image.png"><br></div>
